  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Primary School Girls and Children with Disabilities in the context of the Government&#x2019;s Ebola Transition and Recovery Plan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This programme provides targeted support to up to 7,477 girls and children with disabilities in six operational districts &#x2013; Bo, Kenema, Kailahun, Tonkolili, and Kambia -  helping them return to and remain in formal education after school closures caused by the Ebola crisis disrupted their access to education. The project engages with these children directly, through bursaries and study-groups; with their schools, through support to protection, psycho-social services, and accelerated learning core content roll-out; with their communities through social mobilization; and with the Ministry of Education, Science and Technology for more inclusive schools and improved access to education.</narrative>
  </description>
